            @"9.5	#eSeverability#n.  If the application of any provision of this Agreement to any particular facts or circumstances shall be held to be invalid or unenforceable by an arbitration panel or a court of competent jurisdiction%2C then (a) the validity and enforceability of such provision as applied to any other particular facts or circumstances and the validity of other provisions of this Agreement shall not in any way be affected or impaired thereby%2C and (b) such provision shall be enforced to the maximum extent possible so as to effect the intent of the parties and reformed without further action by the parties to the extent necessary to make such provision valid and enforceable.\r\n9.6	#eRelationship of the Parties#n.  Nothing contained in this Agreement shall be deemed or construed as creating a joint venture%2C partnership%2C agency%2C employment or fiduciary relationship between the parties.  Neither party%2C nor either party's agents%2C have any authority of any kind to bind the other party in any respect whatsoever%2C and the relationship of the parties is%2C and at all times shall continue to be%2C that of independent contractors.\r\n9.7	#eForce Majeure#n.  Neither party shall be responsible or have any liability for any delay or failure to perform to the extent due to unforeseen circumstances or causes beyond its reasonable control%2C including%2C without limitation%2C acts of God%2C earthquake%2C fire%2C flood%2C embargoes%2C labor disputes and strikes%2C riots%2C war%2C acts of a public enemy%2C error in the coding of electronic files%2C Internet or other network ""brownouts"" or failures%2C power failures%2C novelty of product manufacture or other unanticipated product development problems%2C and acts of civil and military authorities.\r\n",
            @"9.8	#eU.S. Government Rights#n.  If you are%2C or are entering into this Agreement on behalf of%2C any agency or instrumentality of the United States Government%2C the Software is ""commercial computer software"" and ""commercial computer software documentation""%2C and pursuant to FAR 12.212 or DFARS 227.7202%2C and their successors%2C as applicable%2C use%2C reproduction and disclosure of the Software is governed by the terms of this Agreement.\r\n9.9	#eExport Controls#n.  You shall abide by all applicable export laws and regulations in its use of the Software.  The Software%2C or any part thereof%2C may not be downloaded or otherwise exported or re-exported (a) into any country for which the United States has a trade embargo%2C or (b) to anyone on the U.S. Treasury Department's list of Specially Designated Nationals or the U.S. Commerce Department's Table of Denial Orders.  You represent and warrant that you are not located in%2C under the control of%2C or a national or resident of any such country or on any such list.\r\n9.10	#eCaptions and Section Headings#n.  The captions and Section and paragraph headings used in this Agreement are inserted for convenience only and shall not affect the meaning or interpretation of this Agreement.\r\n9.11	#eEquitable Relief#n.  You acknowledge and agree that due to the unique nature of this Agreement%2C there can be no adequate remedy at law to compensate Wizet for your breach or threatened breach hereof; that any such breach or threatened breach will allow you or third parties to compete unfairly with Wizet resulting in irreparable harm to Wizet that would be difficult to measure; and%2C therefore%2C that upon any such breach or threat thereof%2C Wizet shall be entitled to injunctive and other appropriate equitable relief (without the necessity of proving actual damages or of posting a bond)%2C in addition to whatever remedies it may have at law%2C hereunder%2C or otherwise.\r\n",
